data/receipts_cache.json
------------------------

Atlas persists parsed receipts here keyed by Gmail Message-ID so subsequent
`main.py receipts` runs don't re-parse + re-download every PDF from IMAP.

Schema:
{
  "<message-id>": {
    "date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "from_addr": "...",
    "subject": "...",
    "amount_cad": 17.99,
    "amount_raw": 17.99,
    "currency": "USD",
    "vendor": "Hostinger",
    "category": "hosting_cloud",
    "attachments": ["Receipt-1234.pdf"],
    "parsed_at": "2026-04-18T01:00:00-04:00"
  },
  ...
}

Delete this file to force a full re-parse of all historical receipts.
Atomic writes (temp file + rename) prevent torn reads if another process
reads mid-update.

Cache is per-year: we key by Message-ID globally but only cache receipts
for the current + previous tax year. Older than that, garbage-collect.
